PUBLIC DOMAIN NOTICE

Eulogikon Ancient Greek Text Corpus

The texts published in this repository are ancient Greek works in the public domain.

Eulogikon makes no copyright claim over its preparation of these texts, including cleaning, normalization, formatting, metadata, manifests, indexes, schema data, layout, or machine-readable structuring.

The purpose of this repository is to store public-domain Greek texts as
published Eulogikon data artifacts for study, teaching, computational analysis,
indexing, and AI ingestion.

PUBLIC DOMAIN STATUS

The underlying ancient Greek works are public domain. They are not licensed by Eulogikon, because Eulogikon does not claim ownership over them.

Where a public-domain mark is required, these texts should be understood as falling under:

https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/

NO COPYRIGHT CLAIM BY EULOGIKON

To the extent that Eulogikon's work involves cleaning, normalizing, arranging, structuring, or presenting public-domain material, Eulogikon makes no copyright claim over that work.

Users may copy, download, print, redistribute, index, transform, analyse, train
on, or otherwise reuse the corpus without seeking permission from Eulogikon.

NO MODERN EDITORIAL MATERIAL

This corpus is intended to contain public-domain Greek texts and Eulogikon's own non-asserted preparation layer. It does not intentionally include modern copyrighted translations, commentary, notes, introductions, apparatus criticus, or proprietary database material.

If any such material is found inadvertently, please notify Eulogikon so that it can be removed or corrected.

ATTRIBUTION

Attribution is appreciated but not required.

A suggested form is:

Text from the Eulogikon Ancient Greek Text Corpus, https://eulogikon.org/

NO WARRANTY

The corpus is provided as-is. Eulogikon does not guarantee that the texts are free from errors, omissions, transcription problems, normalization mistakes, or source contamination.

Users are responsible for checking the text where accuracy is important.